shape: sequence_diagram
vars: {
  d2-config: {
    # layout-engine: elk
    theme-id: 4
  }
}
classes: {
  response: {
    style: {
      stroke-dash: 5
    }
  }
}
user: {shape: person}
app_R: {label: app.R}
server: server.R
chess_py: python-chess (reticulate)
connector: connector API

app_R.note1: |md
  ```
  source utilities (fen_map, find_index_of_rank, …)
  source ui.R and server.R
  read API_URL from env (default http://localhost:8000)
  ```
|
app_R -> shiny: shinyApp(ui, server) on port 3838

server.note1: |md
  ```
  import chess via reticulate
  init reactive values:
  asciiBoard, helperVisual, links, fenDescription, moveHistory
  ```
|

user -> server: select preset FEN or submit FEN
server -> chess_py: board.set_fen(fen)
chess_py -> server: ok {class: response}
server -> connector: "GET /links?fen_string=<FEN>"
connector -> server: "{nodes, edges}" {class: response}
server.note2: |md
  ```
  updateChessDependencies():
  render ASCII board
  call fenMap() for visualization
  generate FEN description (YAML)
  update move history
  ```
|
server -> user: render board + connections + history {class: response}

user -> server: submit move
server -> chess_py: board.push_san(move)
chess_py -> server: ok {class: response}
server -> connector: "GET /links?fen_string=<updated FEN>"
connector -> server: "{nodes, edges}" {class: response}
server -> user: render updated board {class: response}

user -> server: undo
server -> chess_py: board.pop()
chess_py -> server: ok {class: response}
server -> user: render previous position {class: response}
